There are in all siz speeches against Verres, but Aper, according to our MSS„ mentions only five, excluding, as is expressly or tacitly assumed by the commentators, the Actio Prima. But in doing so, Aper would be virtu- ally confessing that he was well aware of the purely literary character of the other five, which cannot possibly have been his intention, for if his censure was to have any foundation at all, it was clearly essential to speak of all the six extant orations as having been actually delivered, and this I believe he did. ’ The archetypon had either VIINVERREM or vnnverrem, which reading, owing to the graphical identity of the numeral and the letter ‘i’ following, caused the evident corruption now existing.
